<div class="card border-info mb-3 mx-auto" style="width 200rem;">
  <h1  class="card-header">About <em>uLearn</em></h1>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="card-text"><strong>uLearn</strong> is an e-commerce website about selling self-paced online courses for others to
      purchase and expand their knowledge or gain more skills. The target demographic is adult learners who are either currently
      working and just want to expand their skills without having to enroll in a school or commit to a certain time. Or students
      who are curious about different subjects that they may not be learning in school.
    </p>
    <p class="card-text">
      This web application is created by <strong>Uncle Sam</strong>, a partnership by two students - Sam Ferrer and Xam Abados, graduating BIT Students
      of Red River College Polytechnic. This is also their Full-Stack Web Development class final project. Below is the database ERD of this web application.
    </p>
  </div>
  <%= image_tag("Ecommerce_ERD.png",class: " card-img-top img-fluid", alt:"uLearn's ERD") %><br/>

  <h2  class="card-header">Table Descriptions</em></h2>
  <div class="container">
  <div class="row row-cols-3">
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">User Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Tracks and stores user password and username that is used for logging in to the site.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Customer Info Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Stores the information of a particular customer assigned to one particular user. And uses the provinces table to assign to retrieve respective taxes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Provinces Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Holds all the provinces and territories of Canada with their corresponding GST, HST, PST rates. These taxes are applied to the user whenever they do a transaction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Orders Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Provides basic information of an order that is associated with the particular customer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Courses In Order Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Stores the courses that were used in a particular transaction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Purchased Course Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Saves the purchased courses details so that whenever a detail changes on a course the transaction details wonâ€™t change.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Courses Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Will contain all the current available courses on the website.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Category Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">Contains all the categories that a course can be assigned. The categories will be updated as time goes on and be used by multiple diff erent courses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card border-secondary mb-3">
        <div class="card-header">Difficulty Table</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">This table will store our difficulty levels that a course can have. These diffi culties can be reused and new diffi culties can be actively created.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
